casebody.data:
Carl J. Caputo v. Alexander O’Bryant (3200)

Dupont, C.P.J., Borden and Cioffi, Js.

Argued May 17 decision released June 18, 1985 Alexander O'Bryant, pro se, the appellant (defendant). Peter L. Truébner and George A. Reilly filed a brief for the appellee (plaintiff). Per Curiam.

We have carefully reviewed the claims of error of the defendant in this case and find them to be without merit.

There is no error.
